<item>
            <title>[SPR-1684] ChainOfResponsibilityFactoryBean; factoryBean which creates a proxy that acts as a COR over a list of objects</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-1684</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?t=21986&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?t=21986&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I keep writing a number of implementations of a single interface and then needing to wrap all those implementations so they are all called. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example, I might have an ErrorHandler interface and a Log4J implementation, then a Mailing implementation etc. and I want them all to fire when invoked.  I would then write a Composite implementation which traversed them all.  This was tiresome so I decided to write a FactoryBean which would do the same thing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attached is the source code.  It may be helpful to others, it might not &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
